the leaderboard with three clears, from Christian Kukuk (Checker 47), Philipp Weishaupt (Zineday) and Richard Vogel (United Touch S).\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9873236641899725, \"rank\": 0.011158097098699717, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9977371022744975, \"rank\": 0.0016968591130848494, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Weishaupt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Weishaupt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Weishaupt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Weishaupt\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Vogel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Richard Vogel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Vogel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Vogel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US finished second on six faults; Karl Cook and Caracole De La Roque and Laura Kraut and Baloutinue jumped clear, and last combination McLain Ward and Ilex picked up four for jumping and two for time.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 590, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997773464358269, \"rank\": 0.0001483548782687305, \"text\": \"US